			<title>Episode 170: Classic Game Analysis - Kohan</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://threemovesahead.libsyn.com/episode-170-classic-game-analysis-kohan]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://quartertothree.com/" target="_blank" class="liexternal" style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px; text-align: left;">Tom Chick</a><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px; text-align: left;">&nbsp;comes back to the show to join Rob and Troy for a look back at one of the great real time strategy series &ndash; Timegate&rsquo;s&nbsp;</span><em style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; color: #333333; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px; text-align: left;">Kohan</em><span style="color: #333333; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 23px; text-align: left;">&nbsp;games. What made Kohan unique and what games, if any, have followed on its original ideas? Is Kohan 2: Kings of War really an inferior sequel? Cities as offensive weapons, the tricks around force posture and the mysteries of who the Kohan are are explored. Also, another one of Tom&rsquo;s stupid quizzes.</span></p>]]></description>
